# [parser-skip]   severity: error
# [parser-skip]   message: "Removed the VLAN ID from the physical NIC / NIC team. The vSwitch external port was set to 'no VLAN' (untagged / access mode at the host NIC level)."
# [parser-skip] 
# [parser-skip] constraint lesson_2026_03_double_vlan_tagging_3:
# [parser-skip]   severity: error
# [parser-skip]   message: "VLAN tagging is now exclusively managed by the Azure Local logical network configuration — a single layer of tagging applied by the SDN stack."
# [parser-skip] 
# [parser-skip] constraint lesson_2026_03_double_vlan_tagging_4:
# [parser-skip]   severity: error
# [parser-skip]   message: "Connectivity restored immediately after the NIC VLAN setting was cleared."
# [parser-skip] 
# [parser-skip] constraint lesson_2026_03_double_vlan_tagging_5:
# [parser-skip]   severity: error
# [parser-skip]   message: "Only one layer owns VLAN tagging. When using SDN logical networks (Azure Local, Hyper-V SDN, NSX-T, etc.), disable VLAN configuration at the physical NIC and vSwitch port level. Let the SDN layer be the sole source of VLAN tags."
# [parser-skip] 
# [parser-skip] constraint lesson_2026_03_double_vlan_tagging_6:
# [parser-skip]   severity: error
# [parser-skip]   message: "Double-tagging is silent. Frames leave the host looking healthy; the problem only manifests at the physical switch where double-tagged frames are dropped without error. Packet captures on the host show correctly tagged frames — captures on the physical switch are necessary to diagnose the issue."
# [parser-skip] 
# [parser-skip] constraint lesson_2026_03_double_vlan_tagging_7:
# [parser-skip]   severity: error
# [parser-skip]   message: "Check NIC advanced properties, not just vSwitch settings. NIC driver-level VLAN settings (visible in Device Manager → NIC → Advanced properties) are independent of Hyper-V vSwitch configuration and easy to overlook."
# [parser-skip] 
# [parser-skip] constraint lesson_2026_03_double_vlan_tagging_8:
# [parser-skip]   severity: error
# [parser-skip]   message: "Document the VLAN ownership model before deployment. Before deploying Azure Local, explicitly document: which layer applies VLAN tags (physical NIC, vSwitch, or SDN logical network), and verify that only one layer has a non-zero VLAN ID configured."
# [parser-skip] 
# [parser-skip] constraint lesson_2026_03_double_vlan_tagging_9:
# [parser-skip]   severity: error
# [parser-skip]   message: "ARP visible but no reply is a hallmark of double-tagging. If you can see outbound ARP frames from a VM on the physical switch but receive no reply, double-tagging or VLAN mismatch is the first thing to check — not firewall rules or routing."
# [parser-skip] 
