# [parser-skip] constraint lesson_2026_03_single_assignment_authority_1:
# [parser-skip]   severity: error
# [parser-skip]   message: "`tech-doc-writer.yml` no longer assigns Copilot directly. It creates the documentation issue unassigned and adds the `documentation` label. The `queue-advance` job in `copilot-pr-lifecycle.yml` is the sole path by which Copilot is assigned (Priority 1: doc debt)."
# [parser-skip] 
# [parser-skip] constraint lesson_2026_03_single_assignment_authority_2:
# [parser-skip]   severity: error
# [parser-skip]   message: "Single assignment authority principle: only one workflow — `copilot-pr-lifecycle.yml` — may assign the Copilot SWE agent. All other workflows create issues (unassigned) and rely on queue-advance for assignment."
# [parser-skip] 
# [parser-skip] constraint lesson_2026_03_single_assignment_authority_3:
# [parser-skip]   severity: error
# [parser-skip]   message: "Added the `copilotBusy` guard to check both issue assignees *and* open PR authors before assigning."
# [parser-skip] 
# [parser-skip] constraint lesson_2026_03_single_assignment_authority_4:
# [parser-skip]   severity: error
# [parser-skip]   message: "One workflow owns assignment. Copilot SWE agent assignment must flow through a single queue manager. Any workflow that creates issues must leave them unassigned and let the queue manager handle assignment."
# [parser-skip] 
# [parser-skip] constraint lesson_2026_03_single_assignment_authority_5:
# [parser-skip]   severity: error
# [parser-skip]   message: "Read-check-write is never atomic. Any queue logic that reads state, checks a condition, and writes based on that check is vulnerable to race conditions when concurrent workflow runs share the same resource. Design around idempotency rather than assuming exclusivity."
# [parser-skip] 
# [parser-skip] constraint lesson_2026_03_single_assignment_authority_6:
# [parser-skip]   severity: error
# [parser-skip]   message: "Concurrent triggers compound the risk. Workflows that trigger on high-frequency events (`check_suite`, `schedule`) are likely to run concurrently. Treat them as concurrent by default."
# [parser-skip] 
# [parser-skip] constraint lesson_2026_03_single_assignment_authority_7:
# [parser-skip]   severity: error
# [parser-skip]   message: "Limbo assignments are silent failures. An issue that is assigned but never started does not produce an error — it simply stalls. Add assignment age monitoring to surface limbo states."
# [parser-skip] 
# [parser-skip] constraint lesson_2026_03_single_assignment_authority_8:
# [parser-skip]   severity: error
# [parser-skip]   message: "Removed Copilot assignment from `tech-doc-writer.yml`; it now creates issues unassigned"
# [parser-skip] 
# [parser-skip] constraint lesson_2026_03_single_assignment_authority_9:
# [parser-skip]   severity: error
# [parser-skip]   message: "Documented single assignment authority in `standards/pr-workflow.md`"
# [parser-skip] 
# [parser-skip] constraint lesson_2026_03_single_assignment_authority_10:
# [parser-skip]   severity: error
# [parser-skip]   message: "Added `copilotBusy` guard (checks both assigned issues and open Copilot PRs) to `copilot-pr-lifecycle.yml`"
# [parser-skip] 
